WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.951
{"en":"--- lesson 21  Daniel Mendoza ","ch":"丹尼尔. 门多萨 "}

2
00:00:04.101 --> 00:00:08.784
{"en":"Boxing matches were very popular in England two hundred years ago. ^ ","ch":"两百年前， 拳击比赛在英国非常盛行。  "}

3
00:00:08.934 --> 00:00:14.243
{"en":"In those days,  boxers fought with bare fists for prize money. ^ ","ch":"当时， 拳击手们不戴手套， 为争夺奖金而搏斗。  "}

4
00:00:14.393 --> 00:00:18.684
{"en":"Because of this,  they were known as 'prizefighters'. ^ ","ch":"因此， 他们被称作“职业拳击手”。  "}

5
00:00:18.834 --> 00:00:29.995
{"en":"However,  boxing was very crude,  for there were no rules and a prizefighter could be seriously injured or even killed during a match. ^ ","ch":"不过， 拳击是十分野蛮的， 因为当时没有任何比赛规则， 职业拳击手有可能在比赛中受重伤， 甚至丧命。  "}

6
00:00:30.145 --> 00:00:38.354
{"en":"One of the most colourful figures in boxing history was Daniel Mendoza,  who was born in 1764. ^ ","ch":"拳击史上最引人注目的人物之一是丹尼尔. 门多萨， 他生于1764年。  "}

7
00:00:38.504 --> 00:00:47.314
{"en":"The use of gloves was not introduced until 1860,  when the Marquis of Queensberry drew up the first set of rules. ^ 1860","ch":"年昆斯伯里侯爵第一次为拳击比赛制定了规则， 拳击比赛这才用上了手套。  "}

8
00:00:47.464 --> 00:00:58.260
{"en":"Though he was technically a prizefighter,  Mendoza did much to change crude prizefighting into a sport,  for he brought science to the game. ^ ","ch":"虽然门多萨严格来讲不过是个职业拳击手， 但在把这种粗野的拳击变成一种体育运动方面， 他作出了重大贡献。 是他把科学引进了这项运动。  "}

9
00:00:58.410 --> 00:01:06.123
{"en":"In his day,  Mendoza enjoyed tremendous popularity.  He was adored by rich and poor alike. ^ ","ch":"门多萨在他的全盛时期深受大家欢迎， 无论是富人还是穷人都对他祟拜备至。  "}

10
00:01:06.273 --> 00:01:12.601
{"en":"Mendoza rose to fame swiftly after a boxing match when he was only fourteen years old. ^ ","ch":"门多萨在14岁时参加了一场拳击赛后一举成名。  "}

11
00:01:12.751 --> 00:01:20.150
{"en":"This attracted the attention of Richard Humphries who was then the most eminent boxer in England. ^ ","ch":"这引起了当时英国拳坛名将理查德. 汉弗莱斯的注意。  "}

12
00:01:20.300 --> 00:01:25.192
{"en":"He offered to train Mendoza and his young pupil was quick to learn. ^ ","ch":"他主动提出教授门多萨， 而年少的门多萨一学就会。  "}

13
00:01:25.342 --> 00:01:31.984
{"en":"In fact,  Mendoza soon became so successful that Humphries turned against him. ^ ","ch":"事实上， 门多萨不久便名声大振， 致使汉弗莱斯与他反目为敌。  "}

14
00:01:32.134 --> 00:01:39.899
{"en":"The two men quarrelled bitterly and it was clear that the argument could only be settled by a fight. ^ ","ch":"两个人争吵不休， 显而易见， 只有较量一番才能解决问题。  "}

15
00:01:40.049 --> 00:01:45.019
{"en":"A match was held at Stilton,  where both men fought for an hour. ^ ","ch":"于是两人在斯蒂尔顿设下赛场， 厮打了一个小时。  "}

16
00:01:45.169 --> 00:01:50.557
{"en":"The public bet a great deal of money on Mendoza,  but he was defeated. ^ ","ch":"公众把大笔赌注下到了门多萨身上， 但他却输了。  "}

17
00:01:50.707 --> 00:01:56.643
{"en":"Mendoza met Humphries in the ring on a later occasion and he lost for a second time. ^ ","ch":"后来， 门多萨与汉弗莱斯再次在拳击场上较量， 门多萨又输了一场。  "}

18
00:01:56.793 --> 00:02:05.917
{"en":"It was not until his third match in 1790 that he finally beat Humphries and became Champion of England. ^ ","ch":"直到1790年他们第3次对垒， 门多萨才终于击败汉弗莱斯， 成了全英拳击冠军。  "}

19
00:02:06.067 --> 00:02:13.963
{"en":"Meanwhile,  he founded a highly successful Academy and even Lord Byron became one of his pupils. ^ ","ch":"同时， 他建立了一所拳击学校， 办得很成功， 连拜伦勋爵也成了他的学生。  "}

20
00:02:14.113 --> 00:02:21.747
{"en":"He earned enormous sums of money and was paid as much as $100 for a single appearance. ^ ","ch":"门多萨挣来大笔大笔的钱， 一次出场费就可多达100英镑。  "}

21
00:02:21.897 --> 00:02:27.233
{"en":"Despite this,  he was so extravagant that he was always in debt. ^ ","ch":"尽管收入不少， 但他挥霍无度， 经常债台高筑。  "}

22
00:02:27.383 --> 00:02:33.711
{"en":"After he was defeated by a boxer called Gentleman Jackson,  he was quickly forgotten. ^ ","ch":"他在被一个叫杰克逊绅士的拳击手击败后很快被遗忘。  "}

23
00:02:33.861 --> 00:02:40.816
{"en":"He was sent to prison for failing to pay his debts and died in poverty in 1836. ^ ","ch":"他因无力还债而被捕入狱， 最后于1836年在贫困中死去。  "}

